### Tables (Grid-Based)

```typescript
// Header with gradient
className="grid py-2 shadow-sm"
style={{ background: 'linear-gradient(to right, #2E5AAC, #25488A)', gridTemplateColumns: '80px 200px 120px 1fr' }}

// Data rows (striping + hover)
className={`grid cursor-pointer hover:bg-forvis-blue-50 transition-colors ${index % 2 === 0 ? 'bg-white' : 'bg-forvis-gray-50'}`}
style={{ gridTemplateColumns: '80px 200px 120px 1fr' }}

// Number cells (right-aligned, tabular)
className={`px-3 py-1.5 text-xs text-right tabular-nums font-medium ${value < 0 ? 'text-red-600' : 'text-forvis-gray-900'}`}
// Format negatives: {value < 0 ? `(${formatAmount(Math.abs(value))})` : formatAmount(value)}
```

Use explicit widths via `gridTemplateColumns`, `cursor-pointer` for clickable rows, `tabular-nums` for numbers, red with parentheses for negatives.

